===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
Originally an {{liushu|3|nocap=yes}}, showing two chariots ({{lang|zh|丙}}). Later {{lang|zh|攴}} was added and a {{lang|zh|丙}} omitted to create the form seen in the Shuowen Jiezi ({{lang|zh|㪅}}), a {{Han compound|ls=psc|𰀒|攴|c1=p|c2=s|t1=two chariots|t2=hand holding a whip; action|abb1=yes|nocap=yes}}. The remaining {{lang|zh|丙}} eventually corrupted into a shape similar to {{lang|zh|雨}}.

